# Normalize all text to LF in the repository.
#
# This project deploys shell scripts and a systemd-driven kiosk to a Linux
# appliance. A CRLF shebang (`#!/usr/bin/env bash\r`) or CRLF inside an install
# heredoc will wedge the install on the device. Forcing eol=lf means a
# contributor on Windows cannot commit CRLF that would break the appliance,
# regardless of their local core.autocrlf setting.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Be explicit for the files that must run on the device.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf
*.html  text eol=lf
*.css   text eol=lf
*.js    text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
*.txt   text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize line endings.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.jpeg  binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.pptx  binary
*.ppt   binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf   binary
